But when Crito tells his tale it is found that Glycerium is really a daughter oi Chremes, by name Pasiphilo, who with her uncle Phania had been shipwrecked on the island of Andros when sailing to Asia in quest oi Chremes many years back. This brings about ahappydinorinunt. Allpartiesarereconciled. Pamphilus receives a handsome dowry with his Pasiphila, and even Dauos is forgiven.
